# Local-only and secrets — never commit
*.local
*.local.md
CLAUDE.local.md
.env
.env.*
!.env.template
# Files that typically hold secret VALUES (the CONTENTS are the risk):
*secret*.json
*secrets*.json
client_secret*.json
service-account*.json
credentials.json
*.secret
.secrets/
secrets/
# Filenames containing "secret" are NOT blanket-ignored. This repo is a secrets *toolkit* —
# scan-secrets.sh, skills/cleanse-secrets, skills/rotate-secret, rules/secrets-as-references.md all
# legitimately carry "secret" in the name and MUST be tracked. A broad `**/*secret*` ignore silently
# dropped them (and once dropped secrets-as-references.md, the always-loaded rule). The value-level
# guard is plugins/core/scripts/scan-secrets.sh, run in CI: it BLOCKS any literal secret value in a
# tracked file regardless of filename — that, not the filename, is what keeps values out.
*.key
*.pem
.DS_Store
scratch/
tmp/

# Local learning-loop capture queue (per-machine; distilled+reviewed output is what's durable)
scheduled-tasks/.learning-queue.tsv
